The easiest way to do this will be to use the Functor arguments of variables.
You use a ElemPointArg as an argument to the evaluation of the variable, with something similar to this pseudo code (use the doxygen to find the actual routines):
// First, get a point locator from the mesh
_pl = _mesh.getPointLocator();
const auto other_elem = _pl.locate_elem(point + (0,1,0));
const ElemPointArg elem_point(other_elem, point + (0,1,0));
const auto value_other_elem = _var(elem_point, determineState());

then this gets you the location at the a point + 1 on the second axis
